Department of Petroleum Resources (DPR) has warned marketers of petroleum products, especially premium motor spirit (PMS) otherwise known as petrol, against product hoarding and price hike during and after the festive season. Stating that the country has sufficient petroleum products nationwide, the spokesperson of the agency, Paul Osu, insisted that there was a need to avoid artificial scarcity.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .